The paper discusses the analysis of citations in scientific articles, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on open access articles and the use of DOIs suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis of citation context and section headings may also be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
